# PR Workflow — Mandatory Babysitting

**After creating or pushing to any PR, immediately read and follow the `babysit` skill.**

Do NOT stop at "PR is up at https://…" and hand back to the user.
Do NOT ask whether to babysit — just do it.

## The full lifecycle every time

0. **Check for open PRs first** → `gh pr list --state open`. If a PR from this session is still open, push the new changes to **that** branch instead of opening a second PR. Never have two in-flight PRs from the same session.
1. **Install the cost hook (once per clone/worktree)** → `bash scripts/install-git-hooks.sh`. The `pre-commit` hook captures review cost into BigQuery on each commit. No `git add`, no staged files.
2. **Create PR** → `gh pr create --base main …` — **always pass `--base main` explicitly, never rely on the default.** `gh pr create` with no `--base` targets the repo's *configured* default branch, which can silently drift away from `main` (incident 2026-07-01: PR #119 auto-merged into a stale feature branch because the repo default branch had been misconfigured — `git log` on the working branch looked correct throughout, so the only symptom was the PR's `baseRefName`). `scripts/check_repo_default_branch.py` (wired into `verify.py --full`) and the `pr-base-branch.yml` CI gate are the two mechanical backstops; `--base main` is the first line of defense and costs nothing to type.
3. **Seed cost ledger (BQ)** → `pr_cost_ledger.py set-meta --pr N --branch <branch>`, then record build cost (`record-build` or `capture-build`) into BQ so `validate --require-build` passes. **Do NOT commit `metrics/pr_cost/`** — the ledger is now in BQ, not git. Zero build cost is a hard failure.
4. **Babysit immediately** — read `/Users/adiniekkajj/.cursor/skills-cursor/babysit/SKILL.md` and follow it using the **batch loop** (each completed push triggers a paid Claude Opus review; minimise push count):
   - **Collect all signals first** → `python3 scripts/pr_triage.py --pr N` enumerates every blocking item in one pass: unresolved inline threads (by author class), failing CI checks, merge/behind-base status, Claude verdict + evidence-confidence score.
   - **Fix everything in one go** — resolve merge conflicts, address ALL unresolved threads, fix ALL failing checks within scope. Do not push after each individual fix.
   - **Reply on every thread** — `gh api repos/{repo}/pulls/{pr}/comments/{id}/replies -f body='fixed in <sha> / won't fix: <reason>'` on each thread before pushing.
   - **Push once** — one commit, one push. This triggers exactly one paid Opus re-review.
   - **Re-collect once** → re-run `pr_triage.py` after the review completes. Only loop again if genuinely new blocking signals appear; do not nitpick-loop on already-approved code.
5. **Wait for operator approval** — do NOT arm auto-merge. Auto-merge is operator-only (`gh pr merge N --auto --squash` is run by the operator after they approve, not by the agent). The agent's job ends at "all checks green, all comments replied, no conflicts" — then hand back to the operator.
6. **Confirm merged** → verify `state == MERGED` **and** `baseRefName == main` (`gh pr view N --json state,baseRefName`) before ending the session. A merge into any other base is a failure even if `state == MERGED`.
7. **Post-merge pull + verify** — after confirmed merged:
   - `git -C /Users/adiniekkajj/Documents/build-workspace/jarvis pull` to bring the squash commit into the main working copy.
   - CI's `pr-cost-finalize.yml` writes `merged_at` + final review cost to BQ automatically.
   - View cost data in Grafana: https://steadyangelfish2985.grafana.net/d/jarvis-dev-cost-v1/jarvis-development
   - Spot-check that expected artifacts landed: doc changes appear, nothing was omitted from the squash.
   - Report what SHA landed. Do NOT skip — the main working copy is what Adi reads; leaving it stale is a miss.

## What "babysitting" is NOT

- Changing CI workflow files just to suppress failures
- Making out-of-scope code changes to fix pre-existing issues
- Marking things done without actually verifying CI output

## Reminders

- `pr_cost_ledger.py validate --pr N --require-build` must pass before merge (reads BQ; zero cost = hard fail)
- The cost ledger lives in BQ (`jarvis_dev`), not in git — `pr-cost-gate.yml` reads BQ via WIF
- Always resolve `CHANGES_REQUESTED` reviews — reply if the concern is already addressed on the branch
- The `auto-merge-on-approval` workflow (`.github/workflows/auto-merge-on-approval.yml`) arms `--auto` when Adi approves, but babysitting still needs to fix CI first
